# AC4: `then` (pipeline if) is recognised as a brancher.
# `x then(a, b)` is the idiomatic pipeline form; it cooks to
# App(App(then, [a, b]), [x]).  Spine flattening + structural
# BranchShape classification must recognise it as an If-shape and
# apply the same narrowing as plain `if`.
#
# `x` is annotated as `number | string`.  In the true branch `x + 1`
# would warn without narrowing; with narrowing `x` is `number` → no warn.
` { type: "(number | string) → number" }
add-one-if-num(x): x number? then(x + 1, 0)

result: add-one-if-num(42)
